## ABOUT THIS REPOSITORY

This repository serves as a comprehensive showcase of my end-to-end Quality Assurance capabilities, spanning Structured Manual Testing Methodology and Modern UI Test Automation.

By bridging the gap between manual test case design and programmatic execution, this portfolio demonstrates a complete understanding of the Software Testing Life Cycle (STLC).

### Core Competencies Demonstrated:

* **SDLC & STLC Integration:** Translating business requirements into structured manual test cases and converting critical regression paths into automated scripts.
* 
**Advanced Test Design:** Hands-on application of Black-Box testing techniques including Boundary Value Analysis (BVA) and Equivalence Partitioning (EP).


* **Page Object Model (POM) Architecture:** Building scalable, maintainable, and decoupled automation frameworks using Python and Playwright.
* **Stateful Authentication Caching:** Implementing advanced automation strategies like storage-state caching to optimize test execution speed.
* 
**Defect & Triage Documentation:** Writing execution-ready test sheets and designing robust runtime error-handling blocks.



---

## FRAMEWORK ARCHITECTURE & AUTOMATION SKILLS

For the automation phase of this portfolio, I developed a scalable, high-velocity testing framework modeled around modern web application architectures.

### 1. Page Object Model (POM)

The framework strictly separates the UI layer from the execution layer to maximize code reusability and minimize maintenance overhead:

* **The Page Layer (`/pages`):** Encapsulates page-specific element locators using Playwright's semantic, user-facing locator APIs (`get_by_placeholder`, `get_by_role`) alongside private class attributes.
* **The Test Layer (`/tests`):** Expresses pure functional test flows and assertions, completely isolated from hardcoded DOM selectors.

### 2. Strategic Execution & Error Handling

* **Lifecycle Management:** Leverages Python context managers to handle browser session closures (`context.close()`, `browser.close()`), ensuring no memory leaks or dangling processes occur upon test failures.
* **Resilient Navigation:** Combines `wait_until="domcontentloaded"` with Playwright's native auto-waiting features to eliminate test flakiness and maximize execution speeds.
* **Defect Capture:** Formulated `try-except` blocks to safely catch `TimeoutError` exceptions, log structural failures, and gracefully bubble up errors to the test runner.

---

## MODULES & TEST SCENARIOS COVERED

### 1) Authentication & Session Management Module

* 
**Manual Scope:** Formulated positive/negative test verification matrix for password complexity validation rules including uppercase, lowercase, numeric, and length constraints.


* **Automation Scope:** Automated the login sequence, captured post-authentication browser cookies/tokens, and cached them into a local configuration artifact (`auth_session.json`). Subsequent tests inject this state to bypass the login UI, speeding up the regression suite.

### 2) Core Workflow & Form Validation Testing

* 
**Manual Scope:** Designed structured execution sheets verifying mandatory fields, boundary edge cases, data input validation, and business logic routing.


* 
**Automation Scope:** Programmed dynamic scripts to interact with business forms, using custom parameters to validate data input persistence and submission states.



